docs.name: Estimated and Actual Earnings (EPS) for ROCKCLIFF RSRCS (V.RCR)
docs.description:
EPS estimates and actuals for ROCKCLIFF RSRCS (V.RCR) per Zacks Research.

Exchage: VSE

Currency: CND

DATE: The date on which earnings per share (EPS) was announced by ROCKCLIFF RSRCS

EPS_MEAN_EST: The mean EPS estimate immediately prior to the announcement of actual earnings.

EPS_ACT: The actual EPS as announced on the given date adjusted as necessary to match accounting methodology assumptions used by the sell side analysts surveyed for EPS_MEAN_EST. (Hence EPS_MEAN_EST and EPS_ACT are directly comparable.) EPS_ACT does not reflect revisions that may have been published later by ROCKCLIFF RSRCS

EPS_ACT_ADJ: The size of the adjustment made to the GAAP EPS to remove non-recurring items and add in employee stock option expenses. EPS_ACT_ADJ is the adjustment that makes EPS_ACT and EPS_MEAN_EST directly comparable. (EPS_ACT = GAAP EPS - EPS_ACT_ADJ.)

EPS_AMT_DIFF_SURP: The EPS surprise amount in per share dollar terms, calculated as EPS_ACT - EPS_MEAN_EST

EPS_PCT_DIFF_SURP: The EPS surprise amount in percentage terms, calculated as 100 x (EPS_ACT - EPS_MEAN_EST)/EPS_MEAN_EST

EPS_STD_EST: The standard deviation of all EPS estimates immediately prior to the announcement of actual earnings.

EPS_CNT_EST: The number of estimates used in the calculation of EPS_MEAN_EST and EPS_STD_EST.

FISC_YEAR: The fiscal year to which this earnings event applies.

FISC_QTR: The fiscal quarter to which this earnings event applies.

CAL_YEAR: The calendar year to which this earnings event applies.

CAL_QTR: The calendar quarter to which this earnings event applies.

PER_END_DATE: The reporting period end date. (YYYYMMDD)

PER_CODE: The fiscal period reference in relation to the most recently reported period. The most recently reported quarter is designated as 0. The prior reported quarter is -1. The quarter before that is -2. Etc. The fiscal period designations roll on each earnings report date, not on calendar period end dates.

Notes: For any observation, the earnings announcement could have occurred before, during or after normal market hours. There are cases when no estimates are available. In this case only the actual EPS is shown (EPS_ACT).

Technical Notes: FISC_YEAR, FISC_QTR, CAL_YEAR, CAL_QTR, PER_END_DATE, PER_CODE should be treated as integers, even though the Quandl API will send them as floats.

Premium Support is available for subscribers of this dataset: premium_support@quandl.com

docs.name: Earnings Announcement Dates for CEMTREX NEW (CTEI)
docs.description:
Estimated announcement dates, estimation parameters and supplemental data (including EPS estimates and previous EPS) for CEMTREX NEW (CTEI) per Zacks Research.

Exchage: OTCBB

Currency: USD

AS_OF : The date on which the information displayed was produced.

PER_END_DATE_FR0 : The end date of the most recently reported fiscal year. (YYYYMMDD)

PER_END_DATE_QR1 : The end date of the next fiscal quarter to be reported. (YYYYMMDD)

EPS_MEAN_EST_QR1 : The Zacks consensus estimated earnings per share (EPS) for the next fiscal quarter to be reported calculated as the arithmetic mean of all individual sell-side EPS estimates using the Zacks proprietary BNRI accounting methodology.

EXP_RPT_DATE_QR1 : The expected report date for the next fiscal quarter's earnings. (QR1) (YYYYMMDD)

EXP_RPT_DATE_QR2 : The expected report date for the fiscal quarter after the next fiscal quarter. (QR2) (YYYYMMDD)

EXP_RPT_DATE_FR1 : The expected report date for the next fiscal year's earnings. (FR1) (YYYYMMDD)

LATE_LAST_FLAG : Indicates whether the report is late and by how long. Values in this field will be one of the following: 0 (not late), 1 (more that 3 days late), 2 (more than 20 days late) or 3 (Unknown).

SOURCE_FLAG : Indicates whether the expected report date comes from a company issued confirmation or from a Zacks mathematical algorithm. Values in this field will be one of the following: 1 (Company confirmed), 2 (Estimated based on algorithm) or 3 (Unknown). This field only applies to the next expected quarterly report date. Expected report dates for fiscal periods further out are considered "Estimated" until company confirmations are received for those dates.

TIME_OF_DAY_CODE : Indicates the time of day when the earnings announcement is expected. Values in this field will be one of the following: 1 (After market close), 2 (Before the open), 3 (During market trading) or 4 (Unknown).

EPS_ACT_QR0 : Actual earnings per share (EPS) for the prior (mostly recently reported) fiscal quarter (QR-0)

PER_END_DATE_QR0 : The end date of the prior (most recently reported) fiscal quarter (QR0) (YYYYMMDD)

EPS_ACT_QRM3 : Actual earnings per share (EPS) for the one year prior fiscal quarter (QR-3)

PER_END_DATE_QRM3 : Period end date for the one year prior fiscal quarter (QR-3) (YYYYMMDD)

Technical Notes: PER_END_DATE_FR0, PER_END_DATE_QR1, EXP_RPT_DATE_QR1, EXP_RPT_DATE_QR2, EXP_RPT_DATE_FR1, EXP_RPT_DATE_FR2, PER_END_DATE_QR0 and PER_END_DATE_QRM3 should be treated as integers, even though the Quandl API will send them as floats.

PER_END_DATE: Period end date

PER_CODE: The fiscal period reference in relation to the most recently reported period. The most recently reported quarter is designated as 0. The previous quarter is designated -1. The quarter before that is -2. Etc. The fiscal period designations roll on each earnings report date, not on calendar period end dates.

PER_FISC_YEAR: The fiscal year to which this earnings event applies.

PER_FISC_QTR: The fiscal quarter to which this earnings event applies.

PER_CAL_YEAR: The calendar year to which this earnings event applies.

PER_CAL_QTR: The calendar quarter to which this earnings event applies.

ACT_RPT_DATE: The date on which sales for the prior period was announced.

LAST_REV_DATE: The date on which the sales estimate was last revised prior to the actual sales report.

SALES_ACT: The actual GAAP sales figure as announced on the report date. SALES_ACT does not reflect later revisions that may have been published later by the company.

SALES_ACT_ZACKS_ADJ: The actual adjusted sales figure as announced on the given date, adjusted as necessary to match accounting methodology assumptions used by the sell side analysts surveyed for SALES_MEAN_EST. (Hence SALES_MEAN_EST and SALES_ACT_ADJ are directly comparable.) SALES_ACT does not reflect revisions that may have been published later by the company.

SALES_MEAN_EST: The mean sales estimate immediately prior to the announcement of actual sales.

SALES_AMT_DIFF_SURP: The sales surprise amount in per share dollar terms, calculated as SALES_ACT_ZACKS_ADJ - SALES_MEAN_EST

SALES_PCT_DIFF_SURP: The sales surprise amount in percentage terms, calculated as 100 x (SALES_ACT - SALES_MEAN_EST)/SALES_MEAN_EST

SALES_CNT_EST: The number of estimates used in the calculation of SALES_MEAN_EST and SALES_STD_EST.

SALES_STD_DEV_EST: The standard deviation of all sales estimates immediately prior to the announcement of actual sales.

Premium Support is available for subscribers of this dataset: premium_support@quandl.com
